summary: A new craftable scaled light armor found under steel category. Available in UNP, CBBE, CBBE-TBBP, BodySlide and offering a wide range of customization from skimpy to badass. 4K and 1K texture resolutions also available for download.
descriptionHtml:
[center][color=#EBF1DD][size=4][i][font=Times New Roman][img]http://static-2.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1415087390.png[/img]
[img]http://static-3.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1412459723.png[/img]

4K Textures are highly recommended!

The HDT versions require [b]HDT High Heels System[/b]. Get it [b][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/36213/?]here[/url][/b]!

TBBP versions require TBBP/HDT supported body, skeleton and animations or xml.

For the recipes to appear in the crafting interface you need to have the crafting manual in your inventory!

You can find the matching crossbow [b][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/58704/?]here[/url][/b]!

[img]http://static-2.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-2-1415087390.png[/img]
[img]http://static-3.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-2-1412459723.png[/img]

A new craftable scaled light armor found under steel category. Available in UNP, CBBE, CBBE-TBBP, BodySlide and offering a wide range of customization from skimpy to badass. 4K and 1K texture resolutions also available for download.

The pouches are optional and add 100 points of extra carry weight.

[img]http://static-2.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-3-1415087390.png[/img]
[img]http://static-3.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1412462830.png[/img]
[youtube]la_0VLmDEX8[/youtube] [youtube]B4rolOpehdA[/youtube]
[youtube]GZQWHhjryyY[/youtube] [youtube]j-ycO8_n75Y[/youtube]
[img]http://static-2.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-5-1415087390.png[/img]
[img]http://static-3.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-3-1412459723.png[/img]

This is the ninth armor of a series that will hopefully reach twenty four armors. The idea originated from Minidresses Collection mod by Tiwa44 who did an awesome job converting some of the long dresses to mini versions.

These armors will not offer any protection in real life so don't use them at home!

There is no guarantee that all the armors will be finished but the creation has been fun so far and there are no plans of stopping.

[b]A big THANK YOU here to all of you guys that endorsed, commented or just played and keep playing using this and the previous mods![/b]

Below are eight different mini dresses by Tiwa44 and the progress with the armors. The image will be updated every time something major changes.

[img]http://static-3.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/61012-1-1442736357.jpg[/img]
[img]http://static-3.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1412460420.png[/img]
[img]http://static-2.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1415095593.png[/img]

If for any reason you can't find the book, type help "Tembtra Thief Crafting Manual" and player.additem xxxxxxxx 1 in the console to get the recipe book manually.

[img]http://static-3.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1413848639.png[/img]

[img]http://static-2.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-4-1415087390.png[/img]
[img]http://static-3.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-2-1412746640.png[/img]

Using HDT Version without HDT High Heels System will cause your game to crash.
Due to the many transparencies of the armors, blood spills appear in places they shouldn't.
One workaround is to use the mod [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/60/?]Enhanced Blood Textures[/url] and set the wounds duration to a minimum.
If you are using HDT HighHeels System and you see weird numbers at the top left of your screen disable the debug info as shown below.

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401335443.jpg[/img] [img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1405232089.jpg[/img]

[img]http://static-3.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1412507195.png[/img]

a) Using any mod manager
b) Manual by extracting the contents of the compressed file in the Skyrim/Data folder

[img]http://static-3.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-2-1412507195.png[/img]

a) Using any mod manager
b) Manual by deleting [b]Tembtra Thief Armor.esp[/b] from the Skyrim/Data folder
and by deleting the folders [b]Tembra Thief[/b] inside the Skyrim/Data/Textures/DX/MiniArmorsCollection/ and Skyrim/Data/Meshes/DX/MiniArmorsCollection/ folders.
